      {
        "paragraph_index": 5,
        "text": "This landmark paper by Ackermann and Schwarzenbach was part of the pioneering work by Gerold Schwarzenbach's group in Zürich on aminopolycarboxylate chelating agents. Their systematic study of EDTA complexes in the late 1940s–1950s laid the foundation for our understanding of polyaminocarboxylate metal chelation, and the remarkably high log K ≈ 18.8 for Cu²⁺–EDTA reflects the exceptional thermodynamic stability conferred by the hexadentate coordination of EDTA around Cu²⁺.",
